\qc\b ABSTRACT\par
\par
\ql\b0 Human Resource Management is one of the most important functional areas in any organization because it directly influences employee records, attendance, payroll, leave administration, performance evaluation, communication, and workforce productivity. In many organizations, these activities are still managed through spreadsheets, paper-based workflows, or disconnected software tools. Such methods often result in duplicate records, delayed approvals, reduced transparency, and increased administrative burden. To address these problems, this mini-project presents the design and development of \b E-HRMS (Enterprise Human Resource Management System)\b0, a full-stack web-based application that centralizes major HR operations within a unified digital platform.\par
\par
The proposed system is developed using \b Angular 21 \b0 for the frontend, \b NestJS 11 \b0 for the backend, and \b PostgreSQL \b0 as the relational database. The application follows a modular architecture and supports different user roles, primarily \b Admin \b0 and \b Employee\b0. Administrators are provided with tools to manage employees, attendance, payroll, leave, training, performance, feedback, notifications, and internal communication. Employees are given self-service access to their profile, leave requests, attendance details, payroll records, assigned training, events, and feedback submission.\par
